For VLAN, I'm going to propose a new patchset bumping to EthernetInterface 1.9.0 to remove current usage of VLanEthernetInterface schema
Who is owning this now?  This patchset has been in review for 7 months.  I'd like to get it either merged, abandoned, or see forward progress.

This commit was not being worked because there was a clash with the vlan feature schema version. 
Now that Jiaqing confirmed that vlan feature is getting reworked, we can go ahead with this commit for updating the IPv6 StatelessAddressAutoConfiguration as per latest schema and latest networkd design.
Changes looks good to me. Need commit message update

Did you test to make sure systemd-networkd gets the configuration you desire? All of the DHCP conf states (v4, v4v6stateless, v6stateless, etc..) have been dropped by phosphor-network.
Should this commit merge I don't believe it will perform the desired actions as written.

@Ravi https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/Redfish.md needs to be updated to list that this property is supported at /redfish/v1/Managers/bmc/EthernetInterfaces/{EthernetInterfaceId}/
const bool should also be fine i think.
Property name StatelessAddressAutoConfig is as per schema
What is the value for DHCPv4 + IPv6 Stateless are enabled?
When dhcpv6 is enabled and user sets slaac enabled, even then v6 should be updated as v6stateless right?
no, v6 stateless setup DHCPv6 to false and sets Ipv6 AcceptRA.

Yes, DHCPEnabled flag disabled then its still be same value "xyz.openbmc_project.Network.EthernetInterface.DHCPConf.both"

IPv6AcceptRA property will be disabled
ec should be passed by reference
ec should be passed by reference
I would rather not see this commit approved. I don't think the functionality is accurate.

please mention which functionality is not accurate?
This commit allows both Stateful/Stateless IPv6 configuration as per redfish schema
I'm approving this, despite my disappointment in the schema.
Please use sdbusplus::message::object_path to construct this.

I don't agree with this.
SLAAC during its discovery phase sends a Router Solicitation.
A router, on the current network segment, responds with a Router Advertisement.
If you have set IPv6AcceptRA=false, systemd.networkd will no longer respond to the RA being returned from the router.
SLAAC needs RA in order to function.
What needs to be disabled is the DHCPv6Client entry.
This was the crux of my now abandoned code changes from over a year ago.
Stateful Address assignment relies on both IPv6AcceptRA=true AND DHCPv6Client=true to operate correctly.
Stateless only requires the Routing Advertisement to be active. It is up to the Routing Advertisement packet to asert the M or the O bit in order to complete DNS functionality. Those bits are not controlled by the BMC, but by the routers IPv6 configuration.

yes i agree Stateless only requires the Routing Advertisement to be active.
StatelessAddressAutoConfig parameter is to allow configuration to accept RA packet 
please try configuration StatelessAddressAutoConfiguration with this patch

I also really don't understand how there is now a schism in the DHCPv6 space.
"Stateful" meant something. Specifically it meant IPv6AcceptRA=true, DHCPv6Client=true, assuming systemd.networkd configuration file nomenclature.
"Stateless" meant IPv6AcceptRA=true, DHCPv6Client=false.
"Disabled" indicated both of these controls would be set false.

Following the above paradigm eliminates the need for the "WithoutRA=solicit" commit I have -1'd for phosphor-network.

Now I have no idea what "Enabled" means here. In addition, according to the Redfish schema there is no "Enabled" DHCPv6OperatingMode entry.

I also don't understand why StatelessAddressAutoConfiguration was added to the schema. It only has an "enabled"/"disabled" mode. Again, SLAAC should only be toggling DHCPv6Client in the systemd.networkd config file. We already had that ability in the "Stateless" DHCPv6OperatingMode  part of the schema.
I feel StatelessAddressAutoConfiguration property rightly added to schema to allow configuration independent of DHCPv6 configuration

My opinion, StatelessAddressAutoConfiguration is a terrible naming convention for a control of Router Advertisement. Enabling/Disabling Router Advertisement does more than controlling SLAAC.

If I'm looking in systemd.networkd(5) I can see enabling/disabling Routing Advertisement is done using IPv6AcceptRA. Nowhere in the description of IPv6AcceptRA is there a mention of SLAAC.

By extension, if I want to enable RA from Redfish, the first place I'm going to look in the schema is something with router and advertisement. I'm not going to think "I need to enable StatelessAddressAutoConfiguration" in order to enable Router Advertisement.

I agree there needs to be a knob to turn on/off RA. This commit allows that knob to be turned. The naming convention for turning that knob leaves a lot to be desired.
You might consider posting your thoughts on https://redfishforum.com/ where the DMTF folks can actually have some impact on the schemas to possibly make them better.

Please write this using the new mechanisms

you would unpack this as "StatelessAddressAutoConfig/IPv6AutoConfigEnabled" and avoid the intermediate object alltogether.
